@database GETCLIP
@FONT COURIER.FONT 13
@INDEX "index.guide/main"
@NODE Main "GETCLIP"
@TOC "rexx.guide/Built-In FUNCTION LIBRARY INDEX"
@{b}GETCLIP()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}GETCLIP(name)@{ub}

Searches @{"the Clip List" LINK "rexx.guide/THE CLIP LIST"} for an entry matching the supplied name parameter, and
returns the associated value string. The name-matching is case-sensitive, and
the null string is returned if the name cannot be found. The usage and
maintenance of Clip List entries is described in the @{"Chapter 9" LINK "rexx.guide/CHAPTER 9"}.

See also: @{"SETCLIP()" LINK "SETCLIP/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        /* Assume 'numbers' contains 'PI=3.14159' */

        say getclip('numbers')          ==>PI=3.14159
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
